2.2 Less than; greater than
Suppose \(\mathbb{F}\) is an ordered field with positive subset \(\mathbb{P}\). Suppose \(a,b \in \mathbb{F}\). Then:

\(a &lt; b\) is defined to mean $ b - a $
\(a \le b\) is defined to mean \(a &lt; b\) or \(a = b\);
\(a &gt; b\) is defined to mean \(b &gt; a\);
\(a \ge b\) is defined to mean \(a&gt;b\) or \(a = b\)
